This article is a presidential determination and waiver issued by President Barack Obama on December 8, 2016. The determination states that the provision of defense articles and services to foreign forces, groups, or individuals supporting U.S. military operations to combat terrorism in Syria is essential to the national security interests of the United States. The prohibitions in the Arms Export Control Act and Title 10 of the United States Code are waived to allow for this transaction. The Secretary of State is delegated the responsibility to consult with and submit reports to Congress for proposed exports, while the Secretary of Defense is responsible for notifying congressional committees before the waiver takes effect.